<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 7:47PM CST  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Comanche, northern Cotton and east central Tillman Counties through
815 PM CST...
At 746 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Grandfield, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lawton, Walters, Geronimo, Grandfield, Chattanooga, Faxon, Loveland
and southern Fort Sill.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 16 and 37.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
